job_history.role_name: Registered Nurse Clinical Care Coordinator- First Aid
job_history.work_description: Provided leadership to staff through coaching, mentoring and remodeling in order to achieve high quality patient care in a safe and customer focused environment. Provided clinical expertise and a resource to clinical staff. Worked closely with management, physician leadership, and staff to optimize patient flow and improve patient care.

Managed Day-to-Day operations, Device-related adverse events training, Medical equipment maintenance and certification, Vaccine inventory and reports, Clinical staff scheduling, Performance reviews, Chart audits, Clinical evaluations.
Provided first aid, Monitored health and sanitation procedures throughout the camp, administered, Presided at all health checks and followed up on any problems seen in the Health Center.

Illinois State University- Mennonite College of Nursing
